                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18451124-170-offence-1 t18451124-cd-41"></join>3rd of Nov</rs>., between twelve and one o'clock, I was in my parlour—a customer came into the shop—I went, and found the prisoner behind the counter, coming on his hands and knees from the place where the till was—I took hold of him, and found the till open, and two 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. pieces, which were there a few minutes before, were gone—there was some copper in the till, which was not gone—I had left the till shut—I searched the pri<lb></lb>soner, but could not find the two pieces—I sent for the officer, who put his fingers into the prisoner's mouth, and took the two 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. pieces out.</rs>
